<br>
The &quot;blues&quot; still hit hard there, but the plat reward is decent.  The Stonebrunt upgrade quests are worthwhile too I think.  I used to place &quot;tickmarks&quot; on a legal pad next my computer to count how many times I died in that Tower .... (19)<br>
<br>
I started in the low 40's and left at 51, with Tess's Whip.  My character was a ranger and I led the majority of the raids, including the Tess kills.<br>
<br>
1.  There are those that listen and those that die quickly.  If you have guildies that stilll &quot;skate&quot; ahead into the pit after the third time you have explained that everyone needs lev, let them cool their heels in PoK for awhile.<br>
<br>
2.  You can not have invis AND invis v. undead on at the same time.  Failure to grasp this will also earn you a trip to the soulbinder in PoK.<br>
<br>
3.  You do NOT need every single key.  If you only loot the fifth floor key and USE it to gain access to the 6th, you will then have access to floors 1-6.<br>
<br>
4.  Your &quot;Gee, I think I'll run ahead and take a peek&quot; newbies will die and/or wipe your party on 4, 5, 6, and 7.  Award points for the largest and/or most creative trains, otherwise have them visit the soulbinder for awhile.<br>
<br>
5.  Your &quot;Gee, I need to click on every single pixel in my field of vision&quot; newbies will quickly find themselves teleported outside of the Tower.  Its best to let these folks entertain the Temple Guardians.<br>
<br>
6.  Not killing Tess after after you spawn her will earn you the title of &quot;Diplomatic Relations Specialist.&quot;  Especially when she starts summoning those people who were xp'n on 5 and 6.  <br>
<br>
7.  Your melees will get a wee bit frantic if Tess charms that 62 cleric you brought with the group.  A little mr buff probably wouldn't hurt.<br>
<br>
8.  Make sure that all your casters have lots of summoned daggers so that they can raise their throwing skill while you fight Tess.<br>
<br>
9.  Let the clerics loot the first few master keys.  You'll thank me later for this.<br>
<br>
